        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 6:54PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 654 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Andrews, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Andrews County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
